  "response": "Water-based fire extinguishers must not be used on electrical equipment. This is primarily because water is a conductor of electricity, and using a water extinguisher on electrical fires can pose a risk of electric shock. For fires involving electrical equipment, it is recommended to use a carbon dioxide (CO2) extinguisher, a dry chemical extinguisher, or a specialized extinguishing agent designed for electrical fires.",
